@startuml
title
<font size=20><b>ScannerService API : getCapabilities() - Destination-based Capabilities</b></font>
<font size=16>Support for TransmissionMode and Destination parameters</font>
end title

box "Workpath App" #FFFFFF
actor User as "Workpath ScanApp"
participant lib as "WorkpathLib"
end box
box "Workpath services " #C9FFB0
    'participant ScanBR as "ScanLet\nBroadcastReceiver"
    participant ScanCP as "ScanLet [provider]\nContentProvider"
    participant ScanAdapter as "ScanLet [adapter]\nScanOptionProfileAdapter"
    'participant ScanIS as "[service]\nScanJob\nIntentService"
    'participant ScanSM as "[service]\nScanJob\nStateMachine"
    participant ScanDS as "DeviceService"

box "Workpath PacMan" #C9FFB0
    participant PacMan as "PacMan"
end box

box "Dune" #aliceblue
participant E2 as "    E2    "
end box

/'
rnote right of User
end note
'/

autonumber
== Get Scan Capabilities ==
alt API 1 (Current) - getCapabilities(Context, Result)
    User -> lib : ScannerService.\ngetCapabilities(Context, Result)
    activate lib
    lib -> lib : Intent intent = create request
    note right of lib #white
    Bundle : {"clientVersion" : 8}
    **// NO transmissionMode**
    **// NO destination**
    end note
    note right of lib #lightblue
    **API 1: No extra parameters**
    Defaults to:
    - transmissionMode = JOB
    - destination = HTTP
    end note
    lib [#0000FF]-> ScanCP : <<IPC>>\n ContentResolver.call(Uri, "get_caps", Bundle)

else API 1 (Advanced) - getCapabilities(Context, TransmissionMode, Result)
    User -> lib : ScannerService.\ngetCapabilities(Context, **TransmissionMode**, Result)
    activate lib
    lib -> lib : Intent intent = create request
    note right of lib #white
    Bundle : {"clientVersion" : 8,
              **"transmissionMode": IMAGE|JOB**}
    **// NO destination (defaults to HTTP)**
    end note
    note right of lib #lightblue
    **API 1 Advanced: Only transmissionMode specified**
    Defaults to:
    - destination = HTTP
    end note
    lib [#0000FF]-> ScanCP : <<IPC>>\n ContentResolver.call(Uri, "get_caps", Bundle)

else <color:red><b>API 2 (Future) - getCapabilities(Context, Destination, Result)</b></color>
    User -> lib : ScannerService.\ngetCapabilities(Context, <color:red><b>Destination</b></color>, Result)
    activate lib
    lib -> lib : Intent intent = create request
    lib -> lib : <color:red><b>intent.putExtra("DESTINATION", destination)</b></color>
    note right of lib #lightgreen
    Bundle : {"clientVersion" : 8,
              <color:red><b>"destination": HTTP|FTP|NETWORK_FOLDER|ME|EMAIL|USB</b></color>}
    **// NO transmissionMode (defaults to JOB)**
    end note
    note right of lib #lightgreen
    <color:red><b>API 2: Destination-specific capabilities</b></color>
    Defaults to:
    - transmissionMode = JOB
    end note
    lib [#0000FF]-> ScanCP : <<IPC>>\n ContentResolver.call(Uri, "get_caps", Bundle)

else <color:red><b>API 2 (Advanced) - getCapabilities(Context, Destination, TransmissionMode, Result)</b></color>
    User -> lib : ScannerService.\ngetCapabilities(Context, <color:red><b>Destination</b></color>, <color:red><b>TransmissionMode</b></color>, Result)
    activate lib
    lib -> lib : Intent intent = create request
    lib -> lib : <color:red><b>intent.putExtra("DESTINATION", destination)</b></color>
    note right of lib #lightgreen
    Bundle : {"clientVersion" : 8,
              <color:red><b>"destination": HTTP|FTP|NETWORK_FOLDER|ME|EMAIL|USB</b></color>,
              <color:red><b>"transmissionMode": IMAGE|JOB</b></color>}
    end note
    note right of lib #lightgreen
    <color:red><b>API 2 Advanced: Full control</b></color>
    Both destination and transmissionMode specified
    end note
    lib [#0000FF]-> ScanCP : <<IPC>>\n ContentResolver.call(Uri, "get_caps", Bundle)
end

activate ScanCP
ScanCP -> ScanCP : extract parameters from Bundle
note right of ScanCP #lightyellow
**Extract parameters with defaults:**

// TransmissionMode (default: JOB)
TransmissionMode transmissionMode = 
    extras != null && extras.containsKey("transmissionMode")
        ? extras.getSerializable("transmissionMode")
        : **TransmissionMode.JOB**;

<color:red><b>// Destination (default: <color:blue>Global.Destination.HTTP</color>)
Destination destination = 
    extras != null && extras.containsKey("DESTINATION")
        ? extras.getSerializable("DESTINATION")
        : Destination.HTTP;</b></color>
end note

ScanCP -> ScanAdapter : getCapabilities(\n  appPackageName,\n  deviceService,\n  transmissionMode,\n  <color:red><b>destination</b></color>)
activate ScanAdapter

note right of ScanAdapter #lightblue
**Destination affects Profile selection:**
- **HTTP**: Uses http profile section
- **FTP/NETWORK_FOLDER**: Uses networkFolder profile section
- <color:red><b>**ME/EMAIL/USB**: Uses jobStorage profile section</b></color>

TransmissionMode filters available options:
- **IMAGE mode**: Limited document formats
- **JOB mode**: Full capabilities
end note

ScanAdapter -> ScanDS : getProfile(appPackageName)
activate ScanDS
opt Not cached (Token & Profile)
    ScanDS [#0000FF]-> PacMan : <<IPC>>\n queryUuidByPackageName\n(appPackageName)
    activate PacMan
    PacMan [#0000FF]--> ScanDS : <<IPC>>\n application UUID
    deactivate PacMan
    ScanDS [#0000FF]-> E2 : GET /cdm/e2WorkpathInterop/v1/appToken/{applicationId}
    activate E2
    note right of ScanDS #white
    Request solution token for authorization
    end note
    E2 [#0000FF]--> ScanDS : solutionToken
    deactivate E2
end opt

ScanDS [#0000FF]-> E2 : GET /ext/scanJob/v1/profile
activate E2
note right of ScanDS #white
GET /ext/scanJob/v1/profile HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer solutionToken
end note
E2 [#0000FF]--> ScanDS : scan profile
deactivate E2
note right of ScanDS #white
**E2 Profile Response:**
{ "base": { "definitions" : [...] },
  **"http"**: { "definitions" : [...] },
  **"networkFolder"**: { "definitions" : [...] },
  <color:red><b>**"jobStorage"**: { "definitions" : [...] }</b></color>
}
// Different sections for different destinations
end note
ScanDS --> ScanAdapter : Return Profile<E2Type>
deactivate ScanDS

ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : createScanAttributesCapsBuilder(\nProfile, transmissionMode, **destination**)
activate ScanAdapter

note right of ScanAdapter #lightyellow
**Profile → Capabilities Conversion:**

1. **Select OptionProfileHelper by destination:**
- HTTP → uses profile.getHttp()
- FTP/NETWORK_FOLDER → uses profile.getNetworkFolder()
- ME/EMAIL/USB → uses profile.getJobStorage()

2. **Filter options by TransmissionMode:**
- IMAGE mode: Only image formats (JPEG, PNG)
- JOB mode: All formats (PDF, TIFF, etc.)

3. **Extract capabilities from Profile**
4. **Convert E2 → Workpath API types**
end note

alt destination is HTTP
 ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : helper = getOptionProfileHelper(profile, **HTTP**)
 ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : extract HTTP-specific capabilities
else destination is FTP or NETWORK_FOLDER
 ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : helper = getOptionProfileHelper(profile, **NETWORK_FOLDER**)
 ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : extract NetworkFolder-specific capabilities
else destination is ME, EMAIL, or USB
 ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : <color:red><b>helper = getOptionProfileHelper(profile, **ME**) // EMAIL or USB</b></color>
 ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : <color:red><b>extract JobStorage-specific capabilities</b></color>
 note right of ScanAdapter #pink
 <color:red><b>ME/EMAIL/USB use JobStorage profile</b></color>
 JobStorage section provides destination-specific capabilities
 end note
end

ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : Filter by transmissionMode:\n- Extract documentFormat list\n- Extract colorMode list\n- Extract resolution list\n- etc.

ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : Convert E2Type to WorkpathAPIType\nusing ScanTypeMapping converters
note right of ScanAdapter #white
**ScanTypeMapping Examples:**
- ColorMode: E2.ColorMode → ScanAttributes.ColorMode
- Resolution: E2.Resolution → Integer (DPI)
- PlexMode + BindingFormat → ScanAttributes.Duplex
end note

ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : Build ScanAttributesCaps object
deactivate ScanAdapter

ScanAdapter -> ScanAdapter : JsonParser.toJson(ScanAttributesCaps)
ScanAdapter --> ScanCP : Return Json String\n(ScanAttributesCaps)
deactivate ScanAdapter

ScanCP -[#0000FF]-> lib : <<IPC>>\n Return Bundle
deactivate ScanCP
note left of ScanCP #white
**Response Bundle:**
{"resultCode": -1,
 "result": ScanAttributesCaps Json String }
end note

lib -> lib : JsonParser.fromJson(jsonStr, ScanAttributesCaps.class)
lib --> User : Return\nScanAttributesCaps
deactivate lib

@enduml
